Children, adults, and geriatric consumers constitute distinct demographic segments with varying preferences for candy types and flavors. The age group segmentation allows manufacturers and retailers to target their products and marketing strategies effectively towards specific consumer groups, tailoring their offerings to meet the unique needs and desires of different age demographics. Moreover, the price point segmentation into economy, mid-range, and luxury categories reflects the diverse pricing strategies employed by market players to cater to consumers across different income brackets and spending capacities.

